<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4896972>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2. Psilotreta voluta sp. nov., the variations of male genitalia: 2A–2H, left lateral process & intermediate appendage of segment X, left lateral; 2I, 2K, 2M, 2O, 2Q, 2S & 2U, phallus, left lateral; 2J, 2L, 2N, 2P, 2R, 2T & 2V, phallus, ventral. Abbreviations: aed. = aedeagus; end. = endotheca; int.app. = intermediate appendage (paired); lat.pr. = lateral process (paired); par. = paramere (paired); phall. = phallotheca; v.pr. = ventral projection (paired)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4896972/files/figure.png" .

