<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4896970>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Psilotreta voluta sp. nov. 1A, male head and pro- and mesothoraces, dorsal; 1B, male right wings, dorsal. 1C–1F, male genitalia: 1C, left lateral; 1D, dorsal (1E, variation); 1F, ventral. 1G–1H, female genitalia: 1G, dorsal; 1H, ventral.Abbreviations: I, II, V = apical forks I, II, V; amw. = anteromesal warts; avs. = anterior vaginal sclerite; a.w. = anterior warts; bsw = basal setal wart (paired); Cu1, Cu1a, Cu1b, Cu2 = cubital veins 1, 1a, 1b and 2; dc = discoidal cell; inf.app. = inferior appendage (paired); int.app. = intermediate appendage (paired); lat.pr. = lateral process (paired); M1, M2, M3, M4 = median veins 1–4; mdp.tX = median dorsal process of tergum X; plw. = posterolateral warts; pr.app. = preanal appendage (paired); pvs. = posterior vaginal sclerite; p.w. = posterior warts; sIX = sternum IX; t.IX = tergum IX; v.pr. = ventral projection (paired)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4896970/files/figure.png" .

